piece of software I use extensively is Double Commander. This is built using Free Pascal, which
will (at last try) run my 1989 "Compact Numerical Methods" codes. If you use optim(), you are
using my "BFGS" (I call it Variable Metric), CG and Nelder-Mead. Brian Ripley asked me in 1995
if he could p2c these for R.

But generally, "old" codes can be difficult to run. I've found quite ancient Fortran can be
run fairly easily on Linux as long as there's not too much input-output. That seems to be
a big obstacle as storage / streaming have changed over the years.

John Nash


