If you reply to me then you should respond to what I wrote, not something else. 

My point was that the software architecture of having readLines read characters from an abstract connection stream that may have been opened in either binary or text mode does not allow the readLines function to enable special handling of line end markers... that has to be handled by the connection because the purpose of text mode vs. binary mode is to hide that messiness.

I did not say it was impossible for the connection object to handle such flexible processing... just that the documentation claim that readLines was handling it based on pre-opened connections with arbitrary mode settings was wrong.

